00:40:24,566 --> 00:40:25,692
Come on, Jackson.

540
00:40:25,734 --> 00:40:26,902
Coming.

541
00:40:49,383 --> 00:40:51,927
Why are you so far away?

542
00:40:51,969 --> 00:40:53,929
I'm right here.

543
00:40:53,971 --> 00:40:56,139
What's the matter?

544
00:40:56,181 --> 00:40:57,683
What's wrong?

545
00:40:57,724 --> 00:41:00,519
I don't understand any of this.

546
00:41:00,561 --> 00:41:02,104
What they're talking about...

547
00:41:02,187 --> 00:41:03,856
it's like they're
speaking in code.

548
00:41:03,897 --> 00:41:06,275
Honey,
it's business,that's all.

549
00:41:07,234 --> 00:41:09,785
Why do you have
to build that plane?

550
00:41:09,820 --> 00:41:13,615
The way you talk about it,
it doesn't even sound like you.

551
00:41:13,657 --> 00:41:15,951
Baby, it's my job.

552
00:41:15,993 --> 00:41:17,202
My job.

553
00:41:18,745 --> 00:41:22,374
You used to say
you'd fly forever.

554
00:41:22,416 --> 00:41:27,379
You used to say they'd have
to bury you in the sky.

555
00:41:27,421 --> 00:41:29,089
Yeah.
They almost did.

556
00:41:36,847 --> 00:41:40,058
What are you looking for
when you look at me like that?

557
00:41:40,100 --> 00:41:42,603
What are you hiding from me?

558
00:41:47,399 --> 00:41:48,525
Nothing.

559
00:42:11,006 --> 00:42:14,468
This is going to be
a little cold.

560
00:42:18,680 --> 00:42:21,683
Let's have a look in here,
shall we?

561
00:42:23,769 --> 00:42:25,229
Ah, there it is.

562
00:42:26,605 --> 00:42:27,773
Let's take a measurement.

563
00:42:31,985 --> 00:42:35,781
Nine weeks,
give or take a few days.

564
00:42:35,822 --> 00:42:37,658
See this here?

565
00:42:37,699 --> 00:42:39,201
This flickering?

566
00:42:39,243 --> 00:42:40,369
What is that?

567
00:42:40,410 --> 00:42:41,912
That's the heartbeat.

568
00:42:46,291 --> 00:42:48,293
Is it supposed to be
moving that fast?

569
00:42:49,503 --> 00:42:52,923
I would be worried
if it were not.

570
00:42:52,965 --> 00:42:54,925
Everything looks fine, Jillian.

571
00:42:59,012 --> 00:43:00,180
Well, that's interesting.

572
00:43:01,974 --> 00:43:03,141
What?

573
00:43:04,518 --> 00:43:05,727
Well, wait.
I'm not sure.

574
00:43:11,275 --> 00:43:13,277
See this here?

575
00:43:13,318 --> 00:43:14,903
What is that?

576
00:43:14,945 --> 00:43:17,072
A second heartbeat.

577
00:43:17,114 --> 00:43:18,615
Two heartbeats.

578
00:43:20,659 --> 00:43:22,995
It's twins, Mrs. Armacost...

579
00:43:23,036 --> 00:43:24,162
twins.

580
00:43:29,209 --> 00:43:32,963
This is a number
of a support group...

581
00:43:33,005 --> 00:43:35,507
for women who are
expecting twins.

582
00:43:38,927 --> 00:43:41,388
There's something
I didn't tell you...

583
00:43:41,430 --> 00:43:42,598
for my chart.

584
00:43:44,308 --> 00:43:46,226
I know I should've, but...

585
00:43:47,644 --> 00:43:50,647
Afew years ago,
after my parents died...

586
00:43:51,648 --> 00:43:52,816
I...

587
00:43:56,695 --> 00:43:58,447
I had a bad time.

588
00:43:59,865 --> 00:44:01,033
How bad, Jillian?

589
00:44:04,745 --> 00:44:07,247
I would see people I knew...

590
00:44:09,541 --> 00:44:10,834
I would see them dead.

591
00:44:12,419 --> 00:44:14,546
And sometimes, I...

592
00:44:16,340 --> 00:44:18,133
I would see myself.

593
00:44:22,179 --> 00:44:23,514
Did you seek treatment?

594
00:44:25,807 --> 00:44:27,351
Were you hospitalized?

595
00:44:36,985 --> 00:44:38,153
Does he know?

596
00:44:40,489 --> 00:44:42,699
He's the one
that got me through it.

597
00:44:42,741 --> 00:44:46,119
You are afraid...

598
00:44:46,161 --> 00:44:47,412
that this pregnancy...

599
00:44:47,454 --> 00:44:49,748
is going to bring
all that back, right?

600
00:44:52,751 --> 00:44:54,795
Spend time with Spencer.

601
00:44:54,837 --> 00:44:56,380
Go through this together.

602
00:44:56,421 --> 00:44:57,840
Now that you know...

603
00:44:57,881 --> 00:44:59,842
that all these feelings
you've been having...

604
00:44:59,883 --> 00:45:02,052
are caused by the life
growing in you...

605
00:45:02,094 --> 00:45:06,932
and by your body adapting to it,
oh, cherish it.

606
00:45:07,975 --> 00:45:12,271
And if you need,
call me any time, day or night.

607
00:45:12,312 --> 00:45:13,897
Thank you.

608
00:45:43,886 --> 00:45:45,762
Just a nightmare, baby.

609
00:45:47,264 --> 00:45:49,766
You were talking in your sleep.

610
00:45:51,602 --> 00:45:52,811
What was I saying?

611
00:45:52,853 --> 00:45:55,105
Couldn't tell.

612
00:45:55,147 --> 00:45:57,983
It didn't sound like words,
really.

613
00:45:58,025 --> 00:45:59,318
It was more like sounds.

614
00:46:00,861 --> 00:46:02,279
I'm scared.

615
00:46:04,573 --> 00:46:07,159
Well, I think it'd be strange...

616
00:46:08,327 --> 00:46:10,954
if a first-time mother
wasn't scared, honey.

617
00:46:16,710 --> 00:46:18,795
Come on.
Come with me.

618
00:46:22,090 --> 00:46:23,217
There you go.

619
00:46:23,258 --> 00:46:25,636
That's better, ain't it?

620
00:46:33,727 --> 00:46:36,146
Everything's going
to be OK, isn't it?

621
00:46:38,899 --> 00:46:41,318
Everything's going
to be just fine, honey.

622
00:46:42,569 --> 00:46:44,530
And they're going
to be healthy, right?

623
00:46:45,739 --> 00:46:48,534
They're going to be beautiful,
just like their mother.

624
00:46:53,080 --> 00:46:54,915
What do you think they'll be
when they grow up?

625
00:46:54,957 --> 00:46:56,500
What are they going to be?

626
00:46:57,793 --> 00:47:00,504
Shit,they going to be
pilots, honey.

627
00:47:00,546 --> 00:47:04,341
Just like their father.

628
00:47:05,592 --> 00:47:07,678
All right, lean back here.

629
00:47:07,719 --> 00:47:09,721
Let me wash your hair.

630
00:47:18,313 --> 00:47:20,190
Am I dreaming, Spencer?

631
00:47:27,406 --> 00:47:29,032
No, you're not dreaming.

632
00:47:32,160 --> 00:47:34,788
And then he gives you
that look...

633
00:47:34,830 --> 00:47:38,292
that "honey, I understand" look.

634
00:47:38,333 --> 00:47:40,127
I don't care how long
he rubs my feet for.

635
00:47:40,169 --> 00:47:42,713
He doesn't understand a thing.

636
00:47:42,754 --> 00:47:44,840
He rubs your feet?

637
00:47:44,882 --> 00:47:46,967
I know what you mean.

638
00:47:47,009 --> 00:47:49,261
We're supposed to be going
through this together...

639
00:47:49,303 --> 00:47:52,306
but I have never felt
more separate from him.

640
00:47:52,347 --> 00:47:54,224
It's like there's something
going on in my body...

641
00:47:54,266 --> 00:47:56,768
he knows nothing about.

642
00:47:56,810 --> 00:47:58,562
He rubs your feet?

643
00:48:00,480 --> 00:48:02,900
I get into the bathtub
with my socks on.

644
00:49:25,524 --> 00:49:27,359
Aah!
Oh, my God!

645
00:49:29,069 --> 00:49:31,280
Jesus, you scared me.

646
00:49:35,868 --> 00:49:38,203
You are in big trouble.

647
00:49:39,663 --> 00:49:40,873
Do you like the pie?

648
00:49:42,082 --> 00:49:44,668
I don't believe I can take
much more of this, honey.

649
00:49:44,710 --> 00:49:46,086
How much do you like the pie?

650
00:49:49,298 --> 00:49:50,507
Come get the pie.

651
00:49:50,549 --> 00:49:53,802
First, I'm going to drink you,
then I'm going to eat you.

652
00:49:53,844 --> 00:49:54,970
Get the pie.

653
00:49:55,012 --> 00:49:57,014
I'm going to eat that, right?

654
00:49:58,432 --> 00:50:00,142
Think you can handle
all three of us?

655
00:50:01,143 --> 00:50:02,269
Do you love the belly?

656
00:50:02,311 --> 00:50:03,437
I love it.

657
00:50:03,478 --> 00:50:05,564
Good,'cause
I love the belly, too.

658
00:50:13,739 --> 00:50:15,157
Excuse me.

659
00:50:26,502 --> 00:50:30,297
Do you remember me?

660
00:50:42,267 --> 00:50:44,603
- How many months?
- Just a few.

661
00:50:45,521 --> 00:50:46,730
I need to speak with you.

662
00:50:47,856 --> 00:50:50,943
Spencer works for McLaren now,
if you're looking for him.

663
00:50:50,984 --> 00:50:55,489
No, I need to speak with you,
Mrs. Armacost...

664
00:50:57,824 --> 00:50:59,952
about those two minutes.

665
00:50:59,993 --> 00:51:03,080
The two minutes, Mrs. Armacost.

666
00:51:03,121 --> 00:51:05,290
What is it, Mr. Reese?

667
00:51:05,332 --> 00:51:08,627
Have you noticed any change
in your husband's behavior...

668
00:51:08,669 --> 00:51:09,920
since the shuttle mission?

669
00:51:09,962 --> 00:51:13,423
I've been through these files,
and there are peculiarities.

670
00:51:13,465 --> 00:51:14,640
Like right here.

671
00:51:14,675 --> 00:51:16,176
This is your husband's
signature...

672
00:51:16,260 --> 00:51:17,845
before he went on the shuttle
that last time...

673
00:51:17,928 --> 00:51:19,847
and here's a form
that he signed when he returned.

674
00:51:19,888 --> 00:51:23,892
Now, they are similar,
but not the same.

675
00:51:23,934 --> 00:51:25,894
Not the same signature.

676
00:51:25,936 --> 00:51:29,565
Mr. Reese, are you in New York
on official NASA business?

677
00:51:29,606 --> 00:51:31,692
And here's the results
of the medical tests...

678
00:51:31,733 --> 00:51:33,485
that we ran when he got back.

679
00:51:35,863 --> 00:51:38,073
Are you on official
NASA business?

680
00:51:38,108 --> 00:51:39,408
Everything is fine.

681
00:51:39,449 --> 00:51:41,034
Everything shows up normal...

682
00:51:41,076 --> 00:51:43,203
but everything's just
a little bit different...

683
00:51:43,245 --> 00:51:44,538
blood levels...

684
00:51:44,580 --> 00:51:46,248
temperature, EKG, EEG.

685
00:51:46,290 --> 00:51:49,293
Everything's just a little off
from what it was. Look.

686
00:51:51,211 --> 00:51:53,088
Does NASA know you're here?

687
00:51:55,299 --> 00:51:56,842
They wouldn't listen.

688
00:51:56,884 --> 00:51:59,678
They terminated my employment.

689
00:52:03,807 --> 00:52:05,767
I have to go now.

690
00:52:05,809 --> 00:52:11,023
If you have anything to say,
call my husband at McLaren.

691
00:52:11,064 --> 00:52:13,692
I showed them the facts, and
they terminated my employment.

692
00:52:13,734 --> 00:52:15,110
They referred me
to a psychiatrist.

693
00:52:15,944 --> 00:52:17,112
Don't follow me.

694
00:52:19,531 --> 00:52:21,241
I've seen Captain Streck's
autopsy report.

695
00:52:21,283 --> 00:52:23,368
It was a massive stroke.
His system overloaded.

696
00:52:23,410 --> 00:52:25,120
His body couldn't stand
the strain.

697
00:52:25,162 --> 00:52:28,165
I've seen Natalie Streck's
autopsy report as well.

698
00:52:30,792 --> 00:52:33,003
That was a suicide.
She killed herself.

699
00:52:33,045 --> 00:52:34,171
I was there.
I saw it.

700
00:52:34,213 --> 00:52:36,256
Yeah, she did,
but according to the report...

701
00:52:36,298 --> 00:52:40,260
when she killed herself,
she was three weeks pregnant.

702
00:52:40,302 --> 00:52:41,553
What did you say?

703
00:52:41,595 --> 00:52:42,804
She probably conceived...

704
00:52:42,846 --> 00:52:44,223
right after her husband
left the hospital.

705
00:52:44,264 --> 00:52:45,891
She was pregnant, Mrs. Armacost.

706
00:52:47,309 --> 00:52:49,436
What happened
during those two minutes...

707
00:52:49,478 --> 00:52:51,104
when they were alone?

708
00:52:51,146 --> 00:52:53,273
The suits that your husband
and Captain Streck wore...

709
00:52:53,315 --> 00:52:55,609
had built-in recorders.
Listen to the voices.

710
00:52:55,651 --> 00:52:57,986
Something happened that scared
the shit out of them.

711
00:52:58,028 --> 00:52:59,780
What could do that?

712
00:52:59,821 --> 00:53:03,158
No. It was an accident.
There was an explosion, and...

713
00:53:03,200 --> 00:53:05,160
No!
They trained for explosions.

714
00:53:05,202 --> 00:53:06,495
They trained for accidents.

715
00:53:06,537 --> 00:53:07,663
They trained
for hundreds of hours.

716
00:53:07,704 --> 00:53:09,206
If something goes wrong,
they have a plan.

717
00:53:09,248 --> 00:53:10,833
They don't panic.
They don't deviate.

718
00:53:10,874 --> 00:53:12,626
They stick to the plan.
That's what they do.

719
00:53:12,668 --> 00:53:14,127
Something happened out there...

720
00:53:14,169 --> 00:53:16,964
that these two men
had not trained for.

721
00:53:17,005 --> 00:53:19,842
What would do that to two
highly-trained astronauts?

722
00:53:19,883 --> 00:53:21,301
Scare them like that?

723
00:53:21,343 --> 00:53:24,346
Can you swear to me
that he's still your husband?

724
00:53:25,681 --> 00:53:28,517
Let go of me, Mr. Reese.

725
00:53:28,559 --> 00:53:30,018
Is this man bothering you?

726
00:53:34,314 --> 00:53:35,482
Yes, he is.

727
00:53:35,524 --> 00:53:39,570
You know, don't you?
You already know.

728
00:53:39,611 --> 00:53:41,947
Room three-oh-four, Nesbit Arms,
Mrs. Armacost.

729
00:53:41,989 --> 00:53:43,574
Please, Mrs. Armacost!

730
00:53:45,450 --> 00:53:48,871
OK. Settle down.
Just settle down.

731
00:53:52,249 --> 00:53:54,877
I'm going to rotate the panel
forty-eight degrees.

732
00:53:54,918 --> 00:53:56,420
You got me, Alex?

733
00:53:56,461 --> 00:53:57,900
Spencer, what is that?

734
00:53:57,935 --> 00:53:59,339
Did you feel that?

735
00:53:59,381 --> 00:54:00,549
Spencer, what is that?

736
00:54:04,720 --> 00:54:07,556
Oh, Jesus Christ!
What the hell is that?

737
00:54:43,884 --> 00:54:46,261
I'm looking for the pregnant
woman in twenty-four-F.

738
00:54:49,848 --> 00:54:51,266
Jillian, what's wrong?

739
00:54:53,227 --> 00:54:56,230
He said she must have
gotten pregnant right...

740
00:54:56,271 --> 00:54:58,232
right after Alex got back.

741
00:54:58,273 --> 00:55:00,025
Did he say anything else?

742
00:55:00,067 --> 00:55:02,736
Oh, God, Nan.

743
00:55:02,778 --> 00:55:06,532
The last thing you need
to worry about is that freak.

744
00:55:06,573 --> 00:55:08,408
Just have Spencer call someone.

745
00:55:08,450 --> 00:55:09,701
No, Nan.

746
00:55:11,954 --> 00:55:14,081
Spencer can't know about this.

747
00:55:14,122 --> 00:55:16,250
But, Jillian,
you said he looked crazy.

748
00:55:16,291 --> 00:55:21,964
You have to promise me
you won't tell Spencer.

749
00:55:22,005 --> 00:55:23,382
Please promise me.

750
00:55:23,423 --> 00:55:26,218
You can't keep these things
bottled inside you, Jillian.

751
00:55:28,971 --> 00:55:30,973
You're right.

752
00:55:36,228 --> 00:55:39,189
If he bothers me again...

753
00:55:39,231 --> 00:55:43,277
I'll tell Spencer, OK?
Deal?

754
00:55:48,657 --> 00:55:50,457
Your table's ready.

755
00:55:50,492 --> 00:55:53,328
Oh, great. All right.
Let's go sit down.

756
00:55:56,123 --> 00:55:59,835
Stan? This year's grand marshal
at the parade of losers?

757
00:55:59,877 --> 00:56:01,086
He's gone.

758
00:56:01,128 --> 00:56:03,839
We can't all be as lucky
as Jill here.

759
00:56:03,881 --> 00:56:05,841
Oh, no.
It's me that's lucky.

760
00:56:11,513 --> 00:56:13,849
You all right, honey?
What's the matter?

761
00:56:16,393 --> 00:56:17,686
What's the matter, honey?

762
00:56:17,728 --> 00:56:19,438
You all right?

763
00:56:19,473 --> 00:56:21,148
Just a little hot.

764
00:56:22,900 --> 00:56:25,652
Why don't you have some water?

765
00:56:28,989 --> 00:56:31,283
I think I'm gonna go home.

766
00:56:42,085 --> 00:56:45,255
All right.

767
00:57:17,037 --> 00:57:18,413
Feeling better?

768
00:57:26,421 --> 00:57:27,548
Where's Nan?

769
00:57:27,589 --> 00:57:29,341
She went out.

770
00:57:29,383 --> 00:57:32,469
It's after midnight.

771
00:57:32,511 --> 00:57:35,430
She's young, Jill.
She's having fun.

772
00:57:35,472 --> 00:57:40,352
Don't you remember
when we used to have fun?

773
00:57:47,734 --> 00:57:49,486
You don't remember that, huh?

774
00:57:54,950 --> 00:57:57,661
All right.

775
00:57:57,703 --> 00:57:59,163
What's wrong with you?

776
00:57:59,204 --> 00:58:02,291
You ever think about
what happened to Alex?

777
00:58:02,332 --> 00:58:04,459
Oh, shit.

778
00:58:04,501 --> 00:58:06,461
What happened to Natalie?

779
00:58:10,340 --> 00:58:12,301
I do, all the time.

780
00:58:13,510 --> 00:58:15,846
Those two minutes
you could have died.

781
00:58:18,265 --> 00:58:21,268
Why do you want to
go back there?

782
00:58:21,310 --> 00:58:23,896
Why do you want to
go back to that?

783
00:58:25,480 --> 00:58:29,193
Can't you just try for once
to be happy? Just once?

784
00:58:45,042 --> 00:58:48,378
I'm gonna go to sleep.

785
00:59:08,607 --> 00:59:10,692
It's Jillian Armacost.

786
00:59:10,734 --> 00:59:13,946
The autopsy
on Natalie Streck...

787
00:59:13,987 --> 00:59:16,114
what did it say
about the baby?

788
00:59:19,409 --> 00:59:21,411
Not on the phone,
Mrs. Armacost.

789
00:59:21,453 --> 00:59:24,414
No, you don't understand.
You have to tell me.

790
00:59:24,456 --> 00:59:27,584
What did Natalie's autopsy
say about the baby?

791
00:59:27,626 --> 00:59:28,961
Babies.

792
00:59:32,881 --> 00:59:34,383
What?

793
00:59:34,424 --> 00:59:38,554
Natalie Streck was pregnant
with twins, Mrs. Armacost.

794
00:59:41,974 --> 00:59:43,350
Oh, my God.

795
00:59:45,936 --> 00:59:47,688
What's happening to me?

796
00:59:47,729 --> 00:59:50,357
You are, too, aren't you?

797
00:59:52,860 --> 00:59:54,736
Pregnant with his twins?

798
00:59:56,613 --> 00:59:58,574
Natalie's babies...

799
01:00:03,120 --> 01:00:05,539
What did the autopsy say
about them?

800
01:00:05,581 --> 01:00:07,499
